OL,6,FThey will have time to process what
OL,7,Fthey have learned before they make
OL,8,Fvictim statements ahead of what the
OL,9,Fjudge said will be a "very difficult
OL,10,Fhearing" for them next week.
OL,12,FWhen the judge asked Richard Dawson,
OL,13,Fdefending, if he had any comments to
OL,14,Fmake, he replied: "Only to express our
OL,15,Fsympathy and condolences to those who
OL,16,Fhave been bereaved in this case."
OL,18,FOn Sunday 30 June, the night before
OL,19,Fthe hearing, members of the community
OL,20,Flit candles in memory of Zackary and
OL,21,FKarlene.
